### 6. KEY PATTERNS & CONVENTIONS

| Pattern | Implementation |
|---------|-----------------|
| **Authorization** | `[Authorize(Roles = "BF Administrator,BF Part Edit,...")]` on controller/action |
| **CSRF Protection** | `[ValidateAntiForgeryToken]` + `@Html.AntiForgeryToken()` in forms |
| **Multiple Buttons** | `[MultipleButtonAction(Name = "action", Argument = "Create")]` to distinguish Create/Edit/Delete from same form |
| **Input Validation** | `[ValidateInput(false)]` to allow HTML in fields; `[ValidateAntiForgeryToken]` |
| **Notifications** | `this.NotifySuccess("msg")` and `this.NotifyError("msg")` from BaseController |
| **Parameterized SQL** | Always use `SqlParameter[]` arrays — never string concatenation |
| **Model Binding** | Forms post `tbl_[Table]_FULL` (ViewModel) to controller actions |
| **Dropdowns** | Populated in controller via `Framework.Functions.Dropdowns.GetBooleanList()` etc. |
| **Grid Component** | `NonFactors.Mvc.Grid` for Index views with filtering, sorting, pagination |
| **Tab UI** | UIKit tabs (`uk-tab`, `uk-switcher`) with custom JavaScript for complex forms |

